Caleb: <i>Tracks lead south.</i>

19
00:01:02,074 --> 00:01:04,211
15, maybe 20 men.

20
00:01:04,246 --> 00:01:06,685
But it don't look like
regular army to me, you know?

21
00:01:09,525 --> 00:01:12,296
Tallmadge. They went south.

22
00:01:12,331 --> 00:01:14,301
Yeah, well, it doesn't
matter. We were too late.

23
00:01:14,335 --> 00:01:17,646
We were late? No, we were lucky.

24
00:01:17,681 --> 00:01:20,121
What, you wanted to turn
up in time for all of this?

25
00:01:20,155 --> 00:01:22,056
The Lord's watching out for us, Ben.

26
00:01:23,526 --> 00:01:26,198
It's like that word your
father used to preach about.

27
00:01:26,232 --> 00:01:27,799
What's that word?

28
00:01:27,834 --> 00:01:30,371
- Providence.
- Yeah, providence.

29
00:01:30,405 --> 00:01:31,640
Look at that.

30
00:01:31,674 --> 00:01:34,882
I found that on the lieutenant there.

31
00:01:34,916 --> 00:01:37,753
Turns out Washington decided
to pardon Hewlett after all,

32
00:01:37,787 --> 00:01:40,595
but the day before these
poor bastards executed him.

33
00:01:40,629 --> 00:01:43,369
And in doing so they've all but signed

34
00:01:43,403 --> 00:01:46,142
the execution order for Abraham in New York.

35
00:01:47,110 --> 00:01:48,916
God, huh? God's watching?

36
00:01:48,950 --> 00:01:52,291
- He's laughing at us.
- Hey, Abe isn't dead yet, all right?

37
00:01:52,326 --> 00:01:55,802
Without Hewlett's word, Abe will hang.

38
00:01:59,343 --> 00:02:02,083
- Three days.
- What?

39
00:02:02,117 --> 00:02:05,223
It'll take three days for news of
this to reach New York at least.

40
00:02:05,257 --> 00:02:08,695
- Yeah, so?
- So we've got three whole days to get into the city,

41
00:02:08,729 --> 00:02:11,765
break Woody out of jail, and
haul his ass back to safety.

42
00:02:11,799 --> 00:02:13,334
- <i> Yeah, three whole days.</i>
- That's right.

43
00:02:13,368 --> 00:02:15,870
Because it only took us three
months to properly infiltrate

44
00:02:15,905 --> 00:02:17,774
a man onto the island in
the first place, right?

45
00:02:17,808 --> 00:02:22,280
Yeah. Well, that was your
plan. This one's mine.

46
00:02:27,392 --> 00:02:29,429
( Chatter )

47
00:02:40,052 --> 00:02:41,389
<i>( branches snapping )</i>

48
00:02:43,192 --> 00:02:44,894
Cold!

49
00:02:44,928 --> 00:02:47,465
Hungry!

50
00:02:47,499 --> 00:02:50,003
<i>We spotted some footprints, Captain,</i>

51
00:02:50,037 --> 00:02:51,908
<i>but they have all their toes.</i>

52
00:02:51,943 --> 00:02:53,344
He can't have gone far.

53
00:02:53,378 --> 00:02:55,845
There ain't a living creature out there.

54
00:02:55,879 --> 00:02:58,249
<i>Ain't no creature 'cept us.</i>

55
00:02:58,283 --> 00:03:01,949
And a pair of frozen cows.
Died recent by their look.

56
00:03:04,452 --> 00:03:08,053
Recall Akinbode. Have
him meet us at the shore.

57
00:03:09,088 --> 00:03:10,689
We're sailing on to Oyster Bay

58
00:03:10,723 --> 00:03:12,423
with orders from Major John André

59
00:03:12,457 --> 00:03:14,156
to hunt down some hidden rebels there.

60
00:03:14,190 --> 00:03:17,895
- Sir?
- Hewlett's no frontiersman.

61
00:03:17,929 --> 00:03:20,263
He could never have
eluded us in good health.

62
00:03:20,297 --> 00:03:24,969
<i>I expect the snowmelt to
reveal his body somewhere.</i>

63
00:03:25,004 --> 00:03:28,035
<i>Perhaps we'll return here in the spring.</i>

64
00:03:31,406 --> 00:03:34,808
( flesh squelching )

